    <item>
      <title>How I&#39;ve run major projects</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/how-i-run-major-projects/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 15 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/how-i-run-major-projects/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;From experience running large projects, I&amp;rsquo;ve developed some personal frameworks that have helped me ship better work.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;start-with-the-outcome&#34;&gt;Start with the outcome&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Before anything else, be clear about what done looks like. A fuzzy goal produces fuzzy results.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;work-backwards&#34;&gt;Work backwards&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Once you know the outcome, reverse-engineer the milestones. What must be true one week before launch? One month before?&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;the-weekly-review&#34;&gt;The weekly review&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Every week, ask: what did I ship, what&amp;rsquo;s blocked, and what do I need to decide?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
